# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Azure OpenAI — 4 secrets required
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# On Replit: set these in the Secrets pane (🔒 in the left sidebar).
#   Secrets are per-workspace, never committed, never copied on remix.
#
# Locally: copy this file to back/.env (already gitignored) and fill in values.
#
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your Azure OpenAI resource endpoint.
# Example: https://my-resource.openai.azure.com/
AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=

# API key from Azure Portal → your OpenAI resource → Keys and Endpoint.
AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Name of the deployment you created in Azure Portal → Deployments.
# When set, ALL get_llm() calls route to this single deployment.
# Example: gpt-4o  (or whatever name you used when deploying the model)
AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=

# API version your deployment supports.
# Example: 2025-04-01-preview
AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Alternative auth — DefaultAzureCredential (local dev only, not Replit)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Leave AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY empty and run `az login` in your terminal.
# Requires Azure role: "Cognitive Services OpenAI User" on the resource.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Azure Document Intelligence (optional — OCR for scanned PDFs)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AZURE_DOCUMENT_INTELLIGENCE_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.cognitiveservices.azure.com/
# FORCE_DOC_INTELLIGENCE=true
